      <data key="d5">The Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 is the main law governing criminal procedure in India. It was enacted to replace the previous criminal procedure law that was in place. The Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 provides the framework for the administration of criminal justice in the country, outlining the powers and duties of the police, the courts, and other authorities involved in the criminal justice system.

