By granting limited arrest powers to private citizens while also mandating a timely transfer of custody to the authorities, Section 40 aims to strike a balance between empowering the public to assist in law enforcement and maintaining the proper procedures and safeguards of the criminal justice system. This provision allows for a more collaborative approach to public safety, where citizens can play a role in apprehending suspected criminals, while still ensuring that the legal process is followed, and the rights of the accused are protected.

