      <data key="d5">The Armed Forces of the Union are a critical component of the national defense and security apparatus of the country. They are referenced in Section 35(1)(g) of the BNSS (Basic National Security Structure) and play a vital role in safeguarding the sovereignty and territorial integrity of the nation.

According to the provided information, no member of the Armed Forces of the Union shall be arrested for anything done or purported to be done by them in the discharge of their official duties, except after obtaining the consent of the Central Government. This provision underscores the importance of the Armed Forces and the need to protect their personnel from undue interference while they carry out their duties.

The Armed Forces of the Union are responsible for a wide range of tasks, including but not limited to, national defense, peacekeeping operations, disaster relief, and humanitarian assistance. They are composed of various branches, such as the Army, Navy, and Air Force, each with its own specialized capabilities and responsibilities.

The Armed Forces of the Union are subject to strict discipline and adherence to the rule of law. They operate under the command and control of the Central Government, ensuring that their actions are aligned with the national security objectives and the Constitution.

The personnel of the Armed Forces of the Union are highly trained and equipped with state-of-the-art technology and weaponry. They undergo rigorous training and are committed to upholding the highest standards of professionalism, integrity, and loyalty to the nation.

In times of crisis or conflict, the Armed Forces of the Union are called upon to defend the country and its citizens. They have a long and proud history of service, having participated in numerous military operations and peacekeeping missions both within the country and abroad.

Overall, the Armed Forces of the Union are a vital component of the nation's security apparatus, playing a crucial role in safeguarding the country's sovereignty, territorial integrity, and the well-being of its citizens.</data>
