The descriptions provided indicate that Section 42 of the BNSS serves to shield members of the armed forces from legal consequences for their actions while carrying out their official duties. This protection is intended to allow the armed forces to fulfill their responsibilities without fear of personal liability, as long as their actions are within the scope of their official roles.

The two descriptions given are not contradictory, but rather complementary, providing a more comprehensive understanding of the purpose and application of Section 42. Both descriptions emphasize that this section of the BNSS is designed to safeguard the members of the armed forces from arrest when they are acting in the course of their official duties, subject to the approval of the Central Government.

