2. Custody during investigation: While Section 167 CrPC dealt with custody during investigation, Section 187 BNSS specifically deals with this aspect.

3. House arrest: Section 187 BNSS has eliminated the possibility of house arrest, which was previously allowed under Section 167 CrPC.

The introduction of Section 187 BNSS was aimed at addressing the shortcomings of the previous Section 167 CrPC. The new section provides a more comprehensive and streamlined approach to the detention of accused persons during investigations, ensuring that the process is more efficient and effective.

Overall, the transition from Section 167 CrPC to Section 187 BNSS represents a significant reform in the legal framework governing the detention of accused persons during investigations. The new section aims to address the challenges faced under the previous provision and provide a more robust and effective system for ensuring the proper administration of justice.</data>
