This ruling has important implications for the conduct of criminal investigations in India. It underscores the need for the investigating agencies to complete their investigations and file chargesheets in a timely manner, as the accused's right to be released on bail may be affected if the investigation drags on.

The case between the CBI and Kapil Wadhawan highlights the complex legal landscape in which the CBI operates. As a premier investigative agency, the CBI is tasked with probing high-profile cases, often involving influential individuals. The outcome of this case has set a precedent that may shape the future conduct of such investigations.

