      <data key="d6">SECTION 42 of the BHARATIYA NAGARIK SURAKSHA SANHITA (BNSS) provides protection to members of the Armed Forces from arrest for actions taken in the discharge of their official duties.

The BNSS is a comprehensive law that governs the rights and responsibilities of Indian citizens. Section 42 of this law specifically addresses the legal protections afforded to members of the Armed Forces.

According to the descriptions provided, Section 42 of the BNSS states that armed forces personnel cannot be arrested for actions they take while carrying out their official duties. This provision is intended to shield military personnel from legal repercussions for decisions and actions made in the course of their service to the country.

The descriptions indicate that this protection applies broadly to the actions of armed forces members, without specifying any limitations or exceptions. The language used suggests that Section 42 offers a robust safeguard for military personnel, allowing them to perform their duties without fear of facing arrest.

By providing this legal shield, Section 42 of the BNSS aims to empower the Armed Forces to effectively carry out their responsibilities in defending the nation. It recognizes the unique challenges and high-pressure situations that military personnel often face, and ensures they can make decisions and take actions as needed without the threat of personal legal consequences.

Overall, Section 42 of the BHARATIYA NAGARIK SURAKSHA SANHITA serves as an important legal protection for members of the Indian Armed Forces, allowing them to fulfill their duties to the country without undue fear of arrest or prosecution. This provision underscores the vital role of the military and the importance of supporting those who serve in its ranks.</data>
